Multi-Converter can use, download, install, update, repair, or uninstall
third-party conversion engines. Those engines are separate third-party
software packages and retain their own licenses, notices, and redistribution
conditions.

The Windows x64 V1 application bundles FFmpeg and ffprobe
8.1.1-essentials_build-www.gyan.dev as base sidecar executables. That build
is configured with --enable-gpl, so the bundled FFmpeg/ffprobe executables are
treated as GPL-covered third-party software in this distribution. Multi-Converter
uses those executables as separate sidecar processes; the AGPL-3.0-or-later
license for Multi-Converter does not replace the FFmpeg/ffprobe licenses.

Each engine archive must include the applicable license files and, when
required or configured, third-party notices for the engine and its bundled
components. The AGPL-3.0-or-later license for Multi-Converter does not automatically
apply to FFmpeg, ffprobe, PDFium, LibreOffice, Pandoc, libvips, 7-Zip,
or any other third-party engine distributed separately.

See docs/THIRD_PARTY_ENGINES.md for the V1 engine notice checklist and
redistribution warnings.
